				 																Art				 																																	 February 25 at Birla Academy of Art amp; Culture; 6 pm: Dr Martin Waelde, director, Max Mueller Bhavan, will inaugurate an exhibition of paintings done by Tinku Das, Lars Ahlstrand, Babita Das and Peter B. Franceschi. This will be followed by a synthesis of four forms of art: Nupurchhanda Ghosh will express the melodious essence by her vocal spirit, Sunil Bhandari will lend the right touch of the mood, Kasturi Mishra will dance on the rhythm and tune, and Babita Das will visualise the peformance through her colours on the canvas.				 																																	 Till February 28 at Gallery Caps, 16 Jatin Bagchi Road, /55; 11 am - 7 pm: To meet the expenses of an open heart surgery to be performed on promising painter and sculptor Debashish Chakraborty, Painters 80 and Gallery Caps present an exhibition-cum-sale of the works of Chakraborty, his wife Anasua and their well-wishers.				 																																	 Till February 26 at Gaganendra Pradarshashala; 2 pm - 8 pm: Sculptures and paintings by Madhusudan Chaudhuri.				 																																	 Till February 27 at Academy of Fine Arts, New South Gallery; 3 pm - 8 pm: Works of Nirmal Dutta.				 																																	 Till March 7 (except Mondays) at Akar Prakar, P-238 Hindustan Park; 11 am - 8 pm: Recent works by Amitava Malakar.				 																																	 Till March 12 (except Sundays) at Galerie 88; 3 pm - 7 pm: Images and Imaginations  works of Akhilesh, Sujata Bajaj, Seema Ghurayya, Ganesh Haloi, Prabhakar M. Kolte, Ram Kumar, S. H. Raza and Laxman Shreshtha.				 																																	 Till March 13 (except Sundays) at CIMA Gallery; Mondays (3 pm - 7 pm), Tuesdays - Saturdays (2 pm - 7 pm): Water colours by Paresh Maity.				 																																	 Till March 2 at Metropolitan Art Salon; 3 pm - 8 pm: Sculptures by Shankar Ghosh.				 																DRAMA				 																													